Business Brief -- Union Carbide Corp.:
   Firm Posts 4th-Period Loss
   As Result of Pretax Charge
For the year, the company reported a net loss of $28
million, or 22 cents a share, compared with net income of
$308 million, or $2.19 a share, for 1990. Sales fell 6.9% to
$4.88 billion from $5.24 billion.
   The $70 million charge included costs tied to the proposed
spinoff of the company's industrial gasses business, expected
to be completed by mid-year.
   Sales for the quarter and year, and year-ago figures
exclude the results of the gasses business. Gasses sales were
up 15% to $617 million in the quarter and 2% to $2.47 billion
in the year.
   The company also took a $13 million pretax charge in the
quarter to cover added costs tied to closing portions of its
Unison transformer services business.